## 🚢 Deployment

### Building for Production

```bash
# Build the application
bun run build

# Run the production build
bun start
```

### Common Deployment Platforms

#### Fly.io

```bash
# Install flyctl
curl -L https://fly.io/install.sh | sh

# Launch your app
fly launch

# Deploy
fly deploy
```

#### Railway

```bash
# Install Railway CLI
npm i -g @railway/cli

# Login and init
railway login
railway init

# Deploy
railway up
```

#### Render

1. Connect your repository at render.com
2. Select "Node" as the environment
3. Set build command: `bun install && bun run build`
4. Set start command: `bun start`

#### DigitalOcean App Platform

1. Connect your repository
2. Configure build command: `bun install && bun run build`
3. Configure run command: `bun start`
4. Set environment variables
5. Deploy

### Production Checklist

- [ ] Set `NODE_ENV=production`
- [ ] Configure all required environment variables
- [ ] Enable health checks
- [ ] Set up monitoring and logging
- [ ] Configure proper resource limits
- [ ] Set up automated backups (if using database)
- [ ] Enable HTTPS/SSL certificates
- [ ] Configure CORS if needed
- [ ] Set up error tracking (Sentry, etc.)

